DURBAN - Police are searching for a Durban ward councillor after he allegedly shot a student.Sabelo Msomi says he and a friend were attacked by the man last week.Msomi had stopped at the councillor's home to help find a girl he had met in the neighbourhood earlier in the day.But he says the man, who was drinking with other people, turned violent and beat the student and his friend. Msomi was shot in the back as he tried to escape.While recovering in hospital, the councillor visited the family home and allegedly offered them a bribe.They refused, and instead reported the case to police.The matter is under investigation, but the Msomi family is worried about their safety.eNCA